<h4 data-index="2782"><span class="red" data-index="2783">Instructions</span></h4>
<p class="latin1" data-index="2784"><span class="label" data-index="2785"><b data-index="2786">a.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Using the information above, prepare a condensed multiple-step income statement. Assume a tax rate of 30% and 100,000 shares of common stock outstanding during 2020.</p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="2787"><span class="label" data-index="2788"><b data-index="2789">b.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Compute comprehensive income for Braun in 2020, assuming Braun had an <span class="char-style-override-15" data-index="2790">unrealized holding loss on an available-for-sale debt investment, net of tax, $12,000</span>.</p>
</div>
