<section data-index="5865">
<h5 data-index="5866"><span class="red" data-index="5867">Accounting</span></h5>
<p data-index="5868"><span data-index="5869">Prepare (a) a single-step income statement for 2020, (b) a retained earnings statement for 2020, and (c)&nbsp;a </span>statement of comprehensive income using the two statement format. Shares outstanding during 2020 were 100,000.</p>
</section>
<section data-index="5870">
<h5 data-index="5871"><span class="red" data-index="5872">Analysis</span></h5>
<p data-index="5873">Explain how a multiple-step income statement format can provide useful information to a financial statement user.</p>
</section>
<section data-index="5874">
<h5 data-index="5875"><span class="red" data-index="5876">Principles</span></h5>
<p data-index="5877">In a recent meeting with its auditor, Counting Crows’ management argued that the company should be able to prepare a non-GAAP income statement with some one-time administrative expenses reported similar to discontinued operations. Is such reporting consistent with the qualitative characteristics of accounting information as discussed in the conceptual framework? Explain.</p>
</section>
</section>
